  "handoff_packets": [
    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nMake the independent reviewer RELIABLY emit the typed <dual_agent_outcome> contract, so proceed_degraded becomes the rare exception again rather than the norm -- restoring a real cross-vendor independent verdict.\\n\\nEXACT PROBLEM: the independent reviewer runs composer-2.5 with a free-text instruction to emit the contract. Even with retries and corrective re-prompts, current Cursor SDK live probes return errored, empty transcripts and fail the contract. Phase 0 evidence in docs/dual-agent/reviewer-contract-reliability-20260531/source/phase0-probe.md shows Cursor SDK plan mode 0/4, Cursor SDK agent mode 0/4, and LiteLLM Gemini 3.1 Pro strict JSON schema 3/3 fidelity-passing outcomes.\\n\\nSCOPE:\\n1. Make independent reviewer model and output enforcement configurable, defaulting to the Phase 0 reliable route.\\n2. Implement the structured LiteLLM/Gemini reviewer path while keeping the existing Cursor SDK path available as explicit compatibility mode.\\n3. Preserve the same typed Outcome contract, evaluate_outcome_fidelity, critical_review completeness, read-only guard, downstream reviewer separation, and real revise/deny blocking semantics.\\n4. Keep reviewer_unavailable_policy recovery for genuine transient infrastructure failures.\\n\\nNON-GOALS: no reviewer registry, no multi-reviewer fan-out, no agentic executor wiring, no durable substrate work, no gate weakening.\\n\\nIMPLEMENTATION STATUS: The structured reviewer route, config/threading changes, Cursor SDK compatibility mode, metadata, and deterministic tests have now been implemented in the working tree. Review the code diff and test receipts as implementation evidence, not plan-only authorization. Do not accept if the diff or tests fail the PRD/TDD contract.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-contract-reliability-20260531/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ac94a81816b02ca55d1dd202eaebd8d5f1a16d9faa8c55c2f2b119785e2a8efc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-contract-reliability-20260531/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ac7a28171fbdc69fb4115dac7c9920f87ae2349b2832c452b156e2b44acf5de2\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-contract-reliability-20260531/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"b887ce379070ccaa062cb15a5c6352e41c9ba479aadd925ae8ae78ed61e84117\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"k